ojectiles are ♥♥♥♥ing T I N Y. The lanteed projectiles are basically invisible when in combat and moving.Some spells are almost useless. The stalacmite thing takes about a second to pop up and then another half second to do damage since it does damage at the end of its animation. This means you gotta baaaaaaait the ♥♥♥♥ out of the enemies. Haste hardly makes a noticeable difference at level 1.FIXED :The crit on next melee attack spell thing only works when it wants to. You can activate it and go whack a few enemies and it'll go off on the third enemy if it wants to.1.4 introduced a lot of fixes for the game, as well as a new UI system, allowing you to have more spells/arrangements available to you. The devs really proved that they're listening to the community with this patch. Crea's becoming something I could get into with a few more bug fixes here and there (and maybe some more early-level mobs).Edits**********Can now move while shielding at all levels. Seems to be a very reasonable pace.Removed bug with shield. Swapping weapon sets while actively blocking with a shield is no longer an issue.FIXED :NEW BUG WITH SHIELD : Can hold right click, left click to remove shield from slot, and still be blocking, even when dropping the shield or placing it in your inventory.FPS Drop issue has been severely reduced. Doesn't happen often anymore.FIXED :New glitch. Sprinting into bow or shield will continue draining stamina while holding the button until stamina runs out or you let go.FIXED :Not really a glitch but a slight quirk : Mashing left and right with sprint unlocked will almost instantly drain your stamina. I imagine this is because the game checks the time between button presses of a direction. This can be easily fixed if you removed the check if the opposite direction is pressed. i.e. If I hit left, start the timer for sprint. If I hit right, cancel the left timer and start the right timer. If I hit left again, cancel right an start left."
