,Recommended,280520,33116226,Posted: 1 July,all,Meymi,"Having only played this game for a few hours, I can already safely say that it's become one of my favourite games to play, easily. Having close to 800 hours clocked on Terraria, Crea excels in a lot of areas, where I feel like Terraria is lacking. Crea's crafting system is really interesting and the outfit/mannequin system is something I haven't seen in any of the games I've played so far. I also love the characters mobility and the possiblity to upgrade it through skill points. Being able to grab onto ledges, swim without the need of extra items (Terraria, I'm glaring at you) and being able to roll right before your face has a meeting with the ground beneath you to prevent a bad case of No-more-life-ingitis.That being said.. so far the only things that I've found out that are bothering me are are really small, but still..-Mob Spawners spawning right next to your house. Not entirely sure if it they'll actually spawn inside your housing, but a few times I've came home from exploring and there's an Oil Slime spawner right in front of my front door. Not that it's a big issue, just.. tiny bit annoying.-Being able to build an actual house. Using the shingles as a roof is great and all, but then when you try to match the blocks that form the rest of the roof with the shingles, it gets complicated. Or in my case so far, impossible. Again, this not a gamebreaking issue, just.. to my eye and the fact that I'm such a perfectionist when it comes to stuff like this, it feels off. After playing Terraria for so long and being able to hammer the blocks to my liking so that the whole roof/building in general matches, it's a little inconvenient. BUT, like I said.. only played a little so far so maybe there will be something that changes that?-Lack of fences/ladders/rope/staircase system (like, for example, in Terraria hammering platforms into a staircase shape)? So far I haven't came across any.All in all, I've tried to sell this game to right about anybody that I know. Love playing it. The atmosphere is amazing, the game is very pleasing to both my eyes and ears which, from me, is a huge plus.TLDR; Love this game to bits so far, I've recommended it to everybody and with time and effort, it can easily surpass Terraria as my favourite game to spend time on."
