,Recommended,280520,18384785,"Posted: 8 October, 2015",all,MR.BONES,"Honestly this game isnt finished but it's still great if you're into the whole Terraria style game. I like this game more than terraria but havent played it as much due to it being early access and all. The heavier focus on the RPG system is what attracts me alot more. There are tons of ways to build your character with the TP (basically skill points) you get, the magi system has been taken down a notch, though I guess it was kind of complicated before. But like I said. You can be a mage, you can be an archer, you can be a fighter, you can be a tank wizard, you can completely avoid combat by just running fast and jumping high. I havent played very much this patch and I dont know if you can still do it, but I used to just stack defense and use the fire aura spell and things would kill themselves on me.The gear crafting is pretty interesting though I'm still not 100% sure how to get the best outcome of it. You an apply different skills when you make an item to give it better stats, but you can use them in different orders for different possible outcomes. There are a good amount of effects you can get on your items such as just raw stats, bonus damage/defence and things like life steal. I hope this gets added onto for things like effect procs such as ""x% chance to cause an ice explosion that slows enemies"" or ""this shield has a x% chance to block 100% of incoming damage"" ect.The combat felt kind of stale when I first started playing, but you can get better combos by investing skill points in certain weapons and what not, you can block which applies your shields defense somehow or another, not 100% sure how it works. You can dodge roll behind things when they try to hit you. But you have to moderate your stamina the whole time or you'll become exhausted and not be able to do much other than walk slowly and jump until your stamina refills. It's honestly a pretty good feeling system. Early game it might feel annoying if you get in a big fight but when you get some more stamina it's not so punishing to just go ham on things.One thing in particular that I really like is that there are portals that spawn that take you to instances like dungeons or just a big area with lots of enemies and sometimes spawners to kill. I havent run into a dungeon yet, that was just recently added but you get some pretty nifty rewards for doing so if I remember correctly. If not just the rare drops that enemy spawners drop.Anyways, the devs update this game alot, I miss the old complicated as heck magic system with tons of different spells, but the new one is still fine and dandy, there are lots of new skills added to other trees such as combat, crafting and exploring. Building is pretty good so far though it's not what I really look forward to doing in these games, exploring is pretty solid, enemies are diverse, there are bosses (which are just bigger badder versions of smaller things) that will randomly spawn and likely wreck you. I think it's very worth buying or adding to your wishlist and keeping an eye on. I straight up love this game and cant wait for it to hit full release."
