76561198042345015,Recommended,280520,23498524,"Posted: 11 June, 2016",all,Tehom,"I would give this game a solid 4/5, which is amazing considering it was just released. Between the levelling system, crafting, skills, and world exploration, this is a must-buy.As far as critiques go, I would say that the skill levelling needs to be tweaked a bit. It is very rare that your crafting level and your player level coincide, resulting in you not being able to use the armor/weapons that you can make or not being able to make the armor/weapons that you need. This takes away a lot of the game's momentum, as it results in you needing to grind crafting recipes or monsters before you can continue to progress. Also, with the crafting system, it's nice that you can pay scrap to learn a recipe if you just can't figure out a couple of the ingredients, but this system would work a lot better if you could just pay 50 scrap to uncover each individual part of a recipe. Also there needs to be a more reliable way to get scrap; the scrapper machine (or whatever it's called) gives like 1 scrap for every 5 or so good items you destroy (totally not worth it).Also, I may be missing something, but it's really hard to use combat skills in combat. If you wanted to use more than 4 combat skills (plus heal), you're basically SOL since your toolbar is full. a toolbar with more slots would help alleviate this problem.Aside from these trivial critiques, the fact remains that this a superb game. More immersive than Terraria and more fun than Edge of Space or even Dig or Die. Buy it while it's on sale!"
