,Recommended,280520,28609846,"Posted: 24 December, 2016",all,Darkness Zombie,"It has been over an year since I posted my negative review on Crea, my main issue about the game having been its performance issues. I am now glad to say that the developers have finally fixed it and, from what I've read, have been working towards improving performance further! I can't say how much more content they've added but I want to shift my negative review into a positive one.It seems they have not only improved the game a lot but they have added a lot of things, too. The title screen is far better, the gameplay more fluid, and hopefully the dungeons and bosses have something more rewarding. Even if they don't I still have to recommend Crea at this point!Why? The leveling system is still highly appealing, the fact that just exploring grants you adventuring EXP to further your exploration skills? It's a nice touch. But this isn't the only reason. The crafting system is really in depth, and isn't the usual 'you automatically know how to do this' stuff. And, lastly, the developers are very involved. The day after my negative posts they were asking for information, even left a tool in game, to try and fix the performance issue.So, again, I feel like Crea is worth it. If you want a good game, with good developers, this is your game.PAST REVIEW: I'm going to be blunt and honest. This game is fun, it has a worthwhile system. Everything you do grinds towards experience, you have a combo system on weapons and you have some neat magic. But, at the same time, it's still only worth being called an ""Early Access"" game. 1.2? It should still be in beta!The resourcing on this game is horrid. I have a 3.4GHZ, twice the minimal, with 8 GBS or ram. My graphics is more than capable but, regardless, I never get above 30 FPS. And the 30? It's there for a second before dropping back down to ten, if not lower. I wanted to like this game, I really did. I played till I even had silver gear! But I can't do it, it's too laggy.The developers do have a good idea of what they're doing but, as a lot of people said, the 'bosses' aren't worth doing. Dungeons are bland. Once they improve on the content and performance of the game? It's worth getting. But as it stands you'd be better off buying Planet Centauri, and it's still in beta. But Terraria is even better.If you can get it for cheap, and I mean less than $5, then I'd say Crea MIGHT be worth it. Otherwise? You're be better off looking elsewhere."
